metadata.name: Tea Rose
metadata.description:
A hybrid of 2 roses is not just a flower...it is the best of them.

The first hybrid tea roses were created in France in the mid-1800s , they exhibit traits midway between their parents, being hardier than the often delicate Tea roses, and with a better ability for repeat-flowering than the more robust Hybrid Perpetuals.
